OL,7,FArmed response police officers in
OL,8,FNorthern Ireland should be provided
OL,9,Fwith head-mounted cameras to ensure
OL,10,Fimproved footage of weapons
OL,11,Fdischarges, the Police Ombudsman has
OL,12,Frecommended. It follows an
OL,13,Finvestigation which found that
OL,14,Ffootage recorded by the shoulder-
OL,15,Fmounted camera of an officer who
OL,16,Ffired a Taser had been obstructed,
OL,17,Fcompromising its evidential value. In
OL,18,Fresponse, a senior PSNI officer said
OL,19,Fthe force's "stark budgetary outlook"
OL,20,Fwas affecting its investment in head-
OL,21,Fmounted cameras.
